Blocks.Text: Structure-based drug design (SBDD) is a well-adopted approach for modern drug discovery.
A key problem in SBDD is to predict whether a candidate drug molecule will bind to the target protein, and how.
The structures of proteins and drug molecules are measured in unit of Angstrom (0.1 nm, 10-10 m).
This extremely small length scale makes the prediction of protein-drug interaction a very challenging task.
